The paper discusses a model for strategic interactions between parties in a complex system, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of game theory and optimization techniques suggests that it could belong to cs.GT (Game Theory) or cs.NE (Networking and Internet Architecture). The focus on complex systems and emergent behavior suggests that it could belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.DS (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The use of percolation theory and forest fires suggests that it could belong to cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
